desc|gcl|wata}}\n* {{desc|gul|wata}}\n* {{desc|icr|waata}}\n* {{desc|jam|wata}}\n* {{desc|kri|wata}}\n* {{desc|bzk|wáta}}\n* {{desc|fpe|wàtá}}\n* {{desc|pis|wata}}\n* {{desc|pih|worta}}\n* {{desc|srm|wáta}}\n* {{desc|srn|watra}}\n* {{desc|tpi|wara}}\n* {{desc|ase|6@Chin|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ca|vàter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|es|váter|bor=1}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{see translation subpage|Noun}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|wateren}}, from {{inh|en|ang|wæterian}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*watrōną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*watrijaną}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*watōr|t=water}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*wódr̥|t=water}}.\n\n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|sco|watter||water}}, {{cog|stq|woaterje|t=to water}}, {{cog|fy|wetterje|t=to water}}, {{cog|nl|wateren|t=to water}}, {{cog|nds-de|watern|t=to water}}, {{cog|de|wässern|t=to water}}, {{cog|da|vande|t=to water}}, {{cog|sv|vattna|t=to water}}, {{cog|is|vatna|t=to water}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{wikidata lexeme|L3303}}\n{{en-verb}}\n[[File:To water the coffee tree in dry season.jpg|thumb|right|A sprinkler '''watering''' ({{senseno|en|pour water onto plants}}) a garden]]\n\n# {{sid|en|pour water onto plants}} {{lb|en|transitive}} To pour water into the [[soil#Noun|soil]] surrounding (plants).\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1900|author=L. Frank Baum|title=The Wonderful Wizard of Oz|chapter=24|passage=Aunt Em had just come out of the house to '''water''' the cabbages when she looked up and saw Dorothy running toward her.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[wet#Verb|wet]] or supply with water; to [[moisten]]; to overflow with water; to [[irrigate]].\n#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Lost|book=9|passage=tears '''watering''' the ground|year=1873}}\n#* {{RQ:Longfellow Evangeline|I\n|passage=Men whose lives glided on like rivers that '''water''' the woodlands.}}\n# {{sid|en|to provide with water}} {{lb|en|transitive}} To provide (animals) with water for [[drink#Verb|drink]]ing.\n#: {{ux|en|I need to '''water''' the cattle.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008| title=Mopus|author=Oisin Curran | page=34| passage=While they '''watered''' and washed their horses, I talked with a red-capped man, some kind of chief.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To get or take in water.\n#: {{ux|en|The ship put into port to '''water'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1944|month=January and February|author=W. McGowan Gradon|title=Forres as a Railway Centre|journal=Railway Magazine|page=23|text=After working the 1.30 p.m. through train from Forres to Aberdeen as far as Elgin, she returns tender first with a local passenger train and is then coaled and '''watered''' at Forres shed, and eventually works back to Perth on the 10.20 p.m. through freight.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|colloquial}} To [[urinate]] onto.\n#: {{syn|en|see [[Thesaurus:urinate]]}}\n#: {{ux|en|[[nature calls|Nature called]], so I stepped into the woods and '''watered''' a tree.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[dilute]].\n#: {{syn|en|water down}}\n#: {{ant|en|refine}}\n#: {{ux|en|Can you '''water''' the whisky, please?}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|dated|finance}} To overvalue (securities), especially through deceptive accounting.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|title=Calls Rail Holding Companies Threat|work=The Sun| date=April 10, 1930| passage=such agencies would make it possible for the railroads to '''water''' stock and evade the law subjecting security issues to public regulation}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To fill with or secrete water or similar liquid.\n#: {{ux|en|Chopping onions makes my eyes '''water'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The smell of fried onions makes my mouth '''water'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To wet and [[calender]], as cloth, so as to impart to it a [[lustrous]] appearance in [[wavy]] lines; to [[diversify]] with wavelike lines.\n#: {{ux|en|to '''water''' silk}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|bewater\n|dewater\n|feed and water\n|overwater\n|overwatered\n|poop water\n|rewater\n|rewatered\n|underwater\n|underwatered\n|unwater\n|unwaterable\n|unwatered\n|waterable\n|water down\n|watered down\n|waterer\n|watering\n|watering can\n|watering hole\n|watering place\n|watering pot\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to pour water into the soil surrounding (plants)}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|سَقَى}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|ջրել}}, {{tt+|hy|ոռոգել}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|sulamaq}}, {{tt|az|suvarmaq}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|поли́вам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|regar}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|淋水|tr=lam4 seoi2}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|澆水|tr=jiāoshuǐ}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|zalít}}, {{tt+|cs|zalévat}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|vande}}\n* Dutch: {{tt|nl|[[water]] [[geven]]}}, {{tt+|nl|sproeien}}, {{tt+|nl|begieten}}, {{t+|nl|wateren}}\n* Dzongkha: {{tt|dz|ཆུ}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|akvumi}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|kastma}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kastella}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|arroser}}\n*: Old French: {{tt|fro|arouser}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{tt|fy|wetter jaan}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|augar}}, {{tt+|gl|regar}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|gießen}}, {{tt+|de|bewässern}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτίζω}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|ἄρδω}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|הִשְׁקָה|tr=hishká}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|öntöz}}, {{tt+|hu|locsol}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|vökva}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|arozar}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|siram}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|valella}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|aquar}}, {{t|ia|abiberar}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|uiscigh}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|annaffiare}}\n* Japanese: {{tt|ja|[[水]][[を]][[やる]]|tr=みずをやる, mizu o yaru}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|magtugtug}}, {{t|pam|tugtugan}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt|ckb|ئاودان|tr=awdan}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|avdan}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|irrigō}}\n* Latvian: {{tt+|lv|laistīt}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|наводнува}}, {{tt|mk|полива}}, {{tt|mk|вади}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|siram}}\n* Mansaka: {{t|msk|tobig}}\n* Naga:\n*: Khiamniungan Naga: {{t|kix|khìam}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|arrouôser}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|vanne}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|asaigar}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|podle