+|ru|пои́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|напои́ть|pf}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|pojiti}}, {{tt+|sh|napajati}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|pojiti}}, {{tt|sl|napajati}}\n* Spanish: {{tt|es|[[dar]] [[agua]] a}}, {{t+|es|abrevar}}, {{t+|es|aguar}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|vattna}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|magpainom}}, {{tt|tl|painumin}}\n* Telugu: {{tt|te|నీరుపెట్టుట}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|su vermek}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|colloquial: to urinate}}\n* Armenian: {{tt|hy|չիշիկ անել}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|пикая}}\n* Chichonyi-Chidzihana-Chikauma: {{tt|coh|ku kodzola}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|vande}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|wateren}}, {{tt+|nl|plassen}}\n* Finnish: {{tt|fi|[[heittää]] [[vesi|vettä]]}}\n* German: {{tt|de|Harn lassen}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|הִשְׁתִּין|tr=hishtín}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|kencing}}, {{tt+|id|buang air kecil}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|おしっこ|alt=おしっこする|tr=oshikko suru}}, {{tt+|ja|小便|alt=小便する|tr=shōben suru}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|mingo}}\n* Norwegian: {{tt+|no|tisse}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|mijar}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|пи́сать|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|попи́сать|pf}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|hacer agua}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|kasta vatten}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|[[சிறுநீர்]] [[பாய்ச்சு]]}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|మూత్రవిసర్జన}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|işemek}}, {{tt+|tr|çiş yapmak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|dilute|water down}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|разреждам}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|spæde ud}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|laimentaa}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|mouiller}} (literally, to wet)\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hígít}}, {{t+|hu|vizez}}\n* Japanese: {{tt|ja|[[水]][[で]][[割る]]|tr=mizu de waru}}, {{tt|ja|[[水]][[で]][[薄める]]|tr=mizu de usumeru}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|разбавля́ть|impf}}, {{tt+|ru|разба́вить|pf}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|diluir}}, {{tt+|es|aguar}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|späda ut}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|magbanto}}, {{tt+|tl|bantuan}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|கல}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to fill with or secrete water}}\n* Armenian: {{qualifier|eyes}} {{tt|hy|արտասվակալել}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|fælde tårer}}, {{tt+|da|græde}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|wateren}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|vuotaa}}, {{tt+|fi|valua}}, {{tt+|fi|kastua}}, {{tt+|fi|kostua}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|pleurer}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|tränen}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|könnyezik}} {{qualifier|eyes}}, {{tt+|hu|nyáladzik}} {{qualifier|mouth}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|menangis}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|濡れる|tr=nureru}} {{qualifier|sexual: to get wet}}, {{tt|ja|[[分泌液]][[を]][[出す]]|tr=bunpitsueki o dasu}} {{qualifier|clinical: to secrete a liquid}}, {{tt|ja|[[水]][[を]][[積み込む]]|tr=mizu o tsumikomu}} {{qualifier|to take on (drinking) water, as a ship in resupply}}\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|pītoritoriwai}} {{qualifier|of the eyes due to irritation such as dryness}}, {{tt+|mi|koe}} {{qualifier|of the mouth}}, {{tt|mi|matatoua}} {{qualifier|Of the eyes}}, {{tt|mi|toriwai}} {{qualifier|of the eyes}}\n* Naga:\n*: Khiamniungan Naga: {{t|kix|khìam}}\n* Norwegian: {{tt+|no|gråte}}, {{tt|no|felle tårer}}\n* Polish: {{qualifier|eyes}} {{tt+|pl|łzawić}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt|pt|[[encher]] [[de]] [[água]]}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|magpaluha}}, {{tt|tl|magluha}}, {{tt|tl|lumuha}}, {{tt|tl|mapaluha}}, {{tt|tl|paluhain}} {{qualifier|eyes}}, {{tt|tl|magtubig}}, {{tt|tl|magkatubig}} {{qualifier|general}}, {{tt|tl|maglaway}}, {{tt|tl|papaglawayin}} {{qualifier|mouth}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஊறு}}\n* Telugu: {{tt|te|పవిత్రజలము}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|sulanmak}}, {{tt+|tr|sulandırmak}}\n* Ukrainian: {{qualifier|очі}} {{tt|uk|сльози́тися}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n<!--Remove this section once all of the translations below have been moved into the tables above.-->\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|dourañ}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|mbo'y}}\n* Hausa: {{t-check|ha|zamzam}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|aquar}}, {{t-check|ia|rigar}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t-check|lt|laistyti}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{commons inline}}\n* {{wikibooks inline}}\n* {{wikiquote inline}}\n* {{wikiversity inline}}\n* {{R:Cambridge}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n* {{R:Collins}}\n* {{R:Dictionary.com}}\n* {{R:MWO}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:OED|pos=n|id=1136754417}}\n* {{R:OED|pos=v|id=1146727277}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aertw|Ewart|tawer}}\n\n{{C|en|Water}}\n\n==Afrikaans==\n{{wp|af:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|af|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|af|id=liquid|:inh|nl:water<id:liquid>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|af|nl|water}}, from {{inh|af|dum|wāter}}, from {{inh|af|odt|watar}}, from {{inh|af|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|af|gem-pro|*watōr}}, from {{inh|af|ine-pro|*wódr̥}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|af|/ˈvɑːtər/}}\n* {{audio|af|LL-Q14196 (afr)-Oesjaar-water.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{af-noun|waters}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n# any artificial fluid similar to water\n# {{lb|af|colloquial}} [[urine]]\n# any body of water, such as a river or a lake\n# a [[disease]] where water is accumulated; [[hydrops]]\n# {{lb|af|in the plural}} a large quantity of water; [[inundation]]\n\n===Verb===\n{{af-verb}}\n\n# to [[urinate]]\n# to [[secrete]] [[liquid]]\n\n===Derived terms===\n* {{l|af|waterbok}} \n* {{l|af|waterlemoen}}\n* {{l|af|ontwater}}\n\n===References===\n* Jan Kromhout, ''Afrikaans-English, English-Afrikaans Dictionary'' (2001)\n\n==Dutch==\n{{wp|nl:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈʋaː.tər/|[β̞aːtər]|q2=Belgium|[ʋaːtər]|q3=Netherlands}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-water (Netherlands).ogg|a=Netherlands}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|aːtər|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|wa|ter}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{root|nl|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|nl|id=liquid|:inh|dum:wāter<id:liquid>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|wāter}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|watar}}, from {{inh|nl|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*watōr}}, from {{inh|nl|ine-pro|*wódr̥}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|n|-s,-@en|+}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}} {{gloss|H<sub>2</sub>O}}\n#: {{uxi|nl|Het '''water''' kookte.|The '''water''' boiled.}}\n# body of water {{gloss|such as a [[lake]], [[ditch]] or [[stream]]}}\n# [[bodily]] [[fluid]] {{gloss|especially [[amniotic fluid]]}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|afvalwater\n|afwaswater\n|badwater\n|bronwater\n|bruiswater\n|chloorwater\n|danswater\n|drinkwater\n|Gods water over Gods akker laten lopen\n|grondwater\n|hemelwater\n|hoogwater\n|ijswater\n|in het water vallen\n|koningswater\n|koolwater\n|kwelwater\n|laagwater\n|leidingwater\n|mineraalwater\n|mondwater\n|Quackjeswater\n|regenwater\n|reukwater\n|rivierwater\n|rozenwater\n|slootwater\n|smeltwater\n|spawater\n|spraakwater\n|suikerwater\n|theewater\n|vaarwater\n|vuurwater\n|waterarm\n|waterballet\n|water bij de wijn doen\n|waterberging\n|waterbouwkunde\n|watercrassula\n|waterdicht\n|waterdier\n|waterdoorlaatbaarheid\n|waterdrager\n|waterdrieblad\n|wateren\n|watereppe\n|waterfiets\n|watergeus\n|waterglijbaan\n|waterhoen\n|waterhond\n|waterhoos\n|waterig\n|waterijs\n|waterinhoud\n|waterjuffer\n|waterkan\n|waterkanon\n|waterkering\n|waterkoker\n|waterkringloop\n|waterleiding\n|waterlobelia\n|waterman\n|watermeloen\n|watermolen\n|water naar de zee dragen\n|waternavel\n|waterpas\n|waterpeper\n|waterplaats\n|waterplant\n|waterpokken\n|waterpolo\n|waterprobleem\n|waterproef\n|waterproof\n|waterput\n|waterrad\n|waterral\n|waterrat\n|waterrietzanger\n|waterrijk\n|waterrijkdom\n|waterschap\n|waterschout\n|waterschouw\n|waterslang\n|watersnood\n|waterspitsmuis\n|watersport\n|waterspreeuw\n|waterspuwer\n|waterstaat\n|waterstand\n|waterstof\n|watertanden\n|watertoren\n|watertrappelen\n|waterval\n|waterverf\n|waterviolier\n|watervlakte\n|watervliegtuig\n|watervogel\n|watervrees\n|watervrij\n|waterweegbree\n|waterwerk\n|waterzooi\n|waterzuring\n|wijwater\n|woelwater\n|zeewater\n|zoet water\n|zout water\n|zwartwater\n|zwemwater\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|water}}\n* {{desc|jvd|water}}\n* {{desc|dcr|watu|water|water|waeter}}\n* {{desc|pey|watter}}\n* {{desc|skw|water}}\n* {{desc|srn|watra|bor=1|unc=1}} {{see desc}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|wateren||bare-verb}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:Van Dale online}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|nl|tarwe}}\n\n{{C|nl|Water}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|fr|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{ellipsis|fr|water-closet}}, borrowed from {{bor|fr|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|watère}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-water.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[toilet]], [[bathroom]]\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|fr|toilettes}}\n* {{l|fr|toilette}} {{q|Belgium}}\n* {{l|fr|waters}}\n* {{l|fr|WC}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|waters}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Hawaiian Creole==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{der+|hwc|en|water}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|hwc|noun}}\n\n# {{tcl|hwc|water|id=Q283}}\n#* {{quote-book|hwc|tlr=Joseph Grimes|title=Da Jesus Book: Hawaii Pidgin New Testament|chapter=Matthew 8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yKgQAQAAIAAJ|publisher=Wycliffe Bible Translators|year=2000|page=110|pageurl=https://ebible.org/study/content/texts/hwcNT/MT8.html|ISBN=978-0-938978-21-3|text=He tell um, “Go.” So dey wen let go da guys, an go take ova da pigs. An you know wat? All da pigs wen run down one steep hill an fall ova da cliff inside da lake, an drown inside da '''water'''.|t=And he said unto them, Go. And they came out, and went into the swine: and behold, the whole herd rushed down the steep into the sea, and perished in the '''waters'''.}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|it|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{pseudo-loan|it|en}}, a clipping of {{der|it|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|vàter<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# [[toilet bowl]]\n# {{lb|it|colloquial}} [[water closet]], [[toilet]]\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Limburgish==\n{{wp|li:}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|li|Waater||Eupen|Krefeld}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|li|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|li|id=liquid|:inh|dum:wāter<id:liquid>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|li|dum|wāter}}, from {{inh|li|odt|watar}}, from {{inh|li|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|li|gem-pro|*watōr}}, from {{inh|li|ine-pro|*wódr̥}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{li-noun|g=n}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n# body of water\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|li|móndjwater}}\n\n===References===\n* Stefaan Top, ''Limburgs sagenboek'' (2004), page 45\n\n==Low German==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nds|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|nds|Drents|Twents}} {{altcase|nds|Water||water}}\n\n==Middle Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|dum|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|dum|id=liquid|:inh|odt:watar<id:water>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|dum|odt|watar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|dum|/ˈwaːtər/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{dum-noun|head=wāter|n}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{dum-decl-noun-st-n|wāter}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|nl|water}}\n* {{desc|li|water}}\n* {{desc|vls|woater}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:VMNW|ID54603}}\n* {{R:MNW|70757}}\n\n{{topics|dum|Liquids}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|enm|watere|watir|waterre}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|enm|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|enm|id=liquid|:inh|ang:wæter<id:water>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|wæter}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*watōr}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈwatər/|/ˈwaːtər/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{enm-noun|pl=wateres}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}} {{gloss|liquid H<sub>2</sub>O}}\n#* {{quote-book|enm|year=c. 1190|author=Layamon|title=Brut|edition=MS. Cotton Caligula A ix|passage=al ſwa great ſwa a beam:<br>þe he leide in ane walle ſtream.<br>Þe ilke makeð þat '''water''' hot:<br>& þan folc halwende.}}\n# {{l|en|water vapour}}, [[condensation]]\n# [[lake]], [[pond]], [[ocean]], [[canal]], body of water\n# water source, [[spring]], [[well]], [[fount]]\n# [[solution]], liquid mixture\n\n====Quotations====\n* {{see citations|enm}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|enm|waterles}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|water}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|en-geo|watter|wetter}}\n* {{desc|sco|watter}}\n* {{desc|yol|waudher|alts=1}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=wā̆ter |pos=n |id=MED51881 |accessdate=2018-03-20}}\n\n{{topics|enm|Beverages|Water}}\n\n==Middle Low German==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|gml|ine-pro|*wed-}}\nFrom {{inh|gml|osx|watar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|gml|/ˈwaːtər/|a=originally}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|gml|noun|g=n|head=wāter}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n#* {{quote-book|gml|year=1537|author=Jürgen Richolff the Younger|title=Datt högeste unde öldeste water recht|section=xxviii|passage=Eyn {{l|gml|schip}} effte twe effte meer liggen in einer hauen dar {{l|gml|kleine|kleyn}} '''water''' is<br>vnde plecht dröge {{l|gml|wēsen|tho synde}}<br>also dat dat eyne schip hart by dem andern tho liggende kumpt {{...}}|translation=A ship or two or more lie in a port with little water, which tends to be dry, so that one the ship comes to lie close by the other {{...}}}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{gml-decl-noun|wāter|wāter|wāteres|wātere|wāter|wāter|wātere|wāteren}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|nds-de|Water}}\n\n==Occitan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|oc|ine-pro|*wed-}}\nShortened form of {{bor|oc|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|oc|noun|g=m}}\n\n# {{lb|oc|colloquial}} [[water closet]], [[toilet]], [[rest room]]\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|water}}, shortening of {{m|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|huáter|hyph=+}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|#s}}\n\n# {{alt sp|es|wáter}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DEA}}"}}